cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY

The paper discusses the limiting effect of the memory wall on parallel speedups, which is a topic related to computer architecture and performance analysis. Therefore, cs.AR (Computer Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes new parallel speedup models, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis, making cs.PF (Performance) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions problem-size variation, communication overhead, and synchronization overhead, which are related to distributed computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the intrinsic characteristics of applications, such as degree of parallelism and susceptibility to the memory wall, which are related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a modeling approach that can be used for scheduling decisions, which involves control theory and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category as well.
